<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A clever Australian mum has revealed how she used an unlikely $2 Kmart product to clean her son's filthy sneakers.</p>

<p>Mum Carman posted photos to the Mums Who Clean Facebook group and said she used Kmart's budget cleaning erasers, which are priced at $2 for a packet of six.</p>

<p>The laundry product is often used to remove stains from walls, material and clothing, but Carman said they worked well at cleaning the shoes too.</p>

<p>A clever Australian mum has revealed how she used an unlikely $2 Kmart product to clean her son's filthy sneakers</p>

<p>'I'm sure everyone knows this but I thought I would share as I'm super impressed,' she said online.</p>

<p>'My son's shoes were gross and dirty from day care so I needed to wash them.</p>

<p>'I used the Kmart cleaning erasers and the white came up great,' she said. </p>

<p>Mum Carman posted photos to the Mums Who Clean Facebook group and said she used Kmart's cleaning erasers, which are priced at $2 for a packet of six</p>

<p>Other shoppers who have previously bought the handy erasers also left positive reviews on the Kmart website.</p>

<p>'Love these erasers, they clean everything especially my shower bases and screens,' one person said.</p>

<p>'These magic erasers are so good for cleaning and so cheap!! Definitely recommend,' another said.</p>

<p>'Handy for cleaning on all surfaces, better than traditional foams,' a third added.</p>

<p>The erasers are available in Kmart stores and online, if stock hasn't sold out prior. </p>

<p>In late August, another mum from Perth, Western Australia said she also used a budget product from Aldi to transform two pairs of well-worn white sneakers and made them look sparkling new (pictured)</p>

<p>In late August, another mum from Perth, Western Australia said she also used a budget product from Aldi to transform two pairs of well-worn white sneakers and made them look sparkling new.</p>

<p>Andrea applied the popular $1.25 Aldi Di-San Stain Remover onto each dirty shoe and soaked the sneakers overnight</p>

<p>Andrea applied the popular $1.25 Aldi Di-San Stain Remover onto each shoe, then used a toothbrush to lightly scrub the surface before soaking the sneakers overnight in another Di-San laundry powder.  </p>

<p>The 'amazing' results spoke for themselves as Andrea shared a before and after photo to the Mums Who Clean Facebook group, which exceeds 271,000 members. </p>

<p>Her social media post has been 'liked' more than 1,500 times by other Australians who were impressed with the end result.</p>

<p>'You are a life saver,' one person said, another added: 'These before and afters are so satisfying'. </p>

<p>Previously other customers have praised Aldi's Di-San Stain Remover spray for it's strong ability to remove though stains from all types of household surfaces, including shower glass, carpets, kitchen counters, splash-backs and ovens. </p>
